      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the deep exhaustion and despair in your words, and it is incredibly brave of you to voice this feeling of hopelessness. When the world feels fundamentally broken and loud, it is natural to feel like there is no future left to fight for. Please know that your pain is real, and it is okay to feel overwhelmed by the weight of it all.\n\nYou are not alone in feeling this way, even if it feels like everyone else is watching or judging you. Sometimes, the noise of the world can drown out our own voices, making it hard to see a path forward. It is important to remember that your worth is not defined by the harshness of the world around you. There are people who care deeply about you and want to help you find a moment of peace.\n\nIf the feeling of hopelessness is becoming too much to carry, please consider reaching out to a mental health professional or a support line. They can offer you a safe space to talk and explore ways to cope with these overwhelming feelings. You matter, and there is hope for finding a moment of calm and connection that feels genuine and safe.",
